# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Psychic Broccoli — Example .http file
# Demonstrates the full Visual Studio .http file syntax
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

// File-level variables (highest priority — override environment variables)
@baseUrl = https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com
@contentType = application/json

// Variables can reference earlier variables
@apiBase = {{baseUrl}}

### List all posts
GET {{apiBase}}/posts

### Get single post
GET {{apiBase}}/posts/1

### Get post with explicit HTTP version
GET {{apiBase}}/posts/2 HTTP/1.1

### Create a post
// @name createPost
POST {{apiBase}}/posts
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Accept-Language: en-US,en;q=0.5

{
  "title": "Hello from Psychic Broccoli",
  "body": "This request was sent from our Tauri HTTP client!",
  "userId": 1
}

### Use the created post's response — request variable chaining
// This demonstrates {{requestName.response.body.$.jsonpath}} syntax.
// You must send "createPost" first to populate its response.
GET {{apiBase}}/posts/{{createPost.response.body.$.id}}

### Update a post (PUT — full replace)
PUT {{apiBase}}/posts/1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "id": 1,
  "title": "Updated title via Psychic Broccoli",
  "body": "Full replacement of the resource",
  "userId": 1
}

### Patch a post (PATCH — partial update)
PATCH {{apiBase}}/posts/1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "title": "Patched title only"
}

### Delete a post
DELETE {{apiBase}}/posts/1

### HEAD request (headers only, no body)
HEAD {{apiBase}}/posts/1

### OPTIONS request
OPTIONS {{apiBase}}/posts

### Get comments for a specific post
GET {{apiBase}}/posts/1/comments

### Get all users
GET {{apiBase}}/users

### Get user by ID
# @name getUser
GET {{apiBase}}/users/1

### Reference a response header from a named request
// Demonstrates {{requestName.response.headers.HeaderName}} syntax
// Send "getUser" first, then this will include its content-type header value
GET {{apiBase}}/todos/1

### Dynamic variable: random integer
// {{$randomInt}} generates a random number (default 0-1000)
// {{$randomInt min max}} generates within a range
GET {{apiBase}}/posts/{{$randomInt 1 100}}

### Dynamic variable: timestamps and dates
// {{$timestamp}}           — Unix epoch seconds (UTC)
// {{$datetime iso8601}}    — ISO 8601 UTC datetime
// {{$datetime rfc1123}}    — RFC 1123 datetime
// {{$datetime "dd-MM-yyyy"}} — custom format
// {{$localDatetime iso8601}} — local timezone
// {{$timestamp 1 d}}       — timestamp + 1 day offset
POST {{apiBase}}/posts
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
X-Request-Id: {{$randomInt 10000 99999}}
X-Timestamp: {{$timestamp}}
X-Date-ISO: {{$datetime iso8601}}
X-Date-RFC: {{$datetime rfc1123}}
X-Date-Custom: {{$datetime "yyyy-MM-dd"}}
X-Date-Local: {{$localDatetime iso8601}}
X-Tomorrow: {{$datetime iso8601 1 d}}
X-Last-Week: {{$datetime "dd-MM-yyyy" -7 d}}

{
  "title": "Post with dynamic variables",
  "body": "Created at {{$datetime iso8601}}",
  "userId": {{$randomInt 1 10}}
}

### Query string parameters in URL
GET {{apiBase}}/comments?postId=1&_limit=5

### Environment-only variable (defined in http-client.env.json)
// The {{Token}} variable comes from the environment file, not this .http file.
// Select an environment from the dropdown in the title bar.
GET {{apiBase}}/posts/1
Authorization: Bearer {{Token}}
